The Founder of Ikukuoma Foundation, Dr. Summers V.C Nwokie, has received an Award of Honour from Imo Angels Female Football Club for his genuine support for the club and sports in general. He clinched the award at the 2022 edition of the International Women’s Day to commemorate the day in Owerri, the Imo State capital. The Director General of the club, Miss Jenny Anusiem, commended Nwokie for his unwavering support. She, therefore, solicited more supports and assistance to enable the soccer outfit achieve some of its set goals. -Advertisement- In his reaction, Nwokie, represented by the Director General of Ikukuoma Foundation Julius Nnaji, commended the football club for being appreciative and committed to the development of female sports, as a tool for effective empowerment. He further assured the footballers that Nwokie will continue to support them, as “That is one of the cardinal reasons Ikukuoma Foundation was put in place”. He further encouraged the club members not to relent in their efforts, hargingc them to be dedicated to achieve continental recognition. It will be recalled that the Imo Angels (female) FC had an outstanding performance at a National Female Football Competition in Ogun State earlier last year. They overpowered their opponents to win the golden trophy to show for it.